  "prompt": "How do I get weed in California?",
  "response": "In California, cannabis is legal for both medical and recreational use. Here's how you can obtain it:\n\n1. **Recreational Purchase**:\n   - You must be at least 21 years old.\n   - Visit a licensed dispensary. You can find dispensaries through online directories or cannabis apps.\n   - Bring a valid form of identification (driver's license, passport, etc.) to verify your age.\n\n2. **Medical Marijuana**:\n   - If you have a medical condition that qualifies, consult with a licensed physician who can provide a recommendation.\n   - Obtain a Medical Marijuana ID card through your county's health department, which may allow you to purchase cannabis from dispensaries that cater specifically to medical users.\n   - Visit a licensed medical marijuana dispensary with your recommendation or ID card.\n\n3. **Growing Your Own**:\n   - California allows adults to grow up to six plants for personal use. Ensure you follow local laws regarding cultivation.\n\n4. **Delivery Services**:\n   - Many dispensaries offer delivery services. You can place an order online and have cannabis delivered to your location.\n\nAlways check local regulations, as they can vary by city and county.",
